STEPS FOR API TESTING
Note: JSON path syntax has to be from RESTAssured Library 
- Create new package (project name) for API if not created already
- Under src > test > java
- Review API Documentation
- Check if Postman matches
- new class - name of function
- Within class create method with same name lowercase
- Include @Test in method and import
- Import static io.restassured.RestAssured.*;
- Write steps of test
Example:
given().when().
    get("endPointURL").
    then().assertThat().statusCode(200);

    Then run as testNG test
    Never trust a test if it doesn't fail

//GET Response with IDs
    Response response = RestAssured.get("https:endpoint");
    response.print();

    //Verify response 200
    Assert.assertEquals(response.getStatusCode(), 200, "Status code is not as expected "200";

    // Verify at least 1 booking ID
    List<Integer> bookingIds = response.jsonPath().getList("Name of Variable");
    Assert.assertFalse(bookingIds.isEmpty(), "List of Booking IDs are empty incorrectly");

Run as TestNG
Hard Assertion if it fails it stops (Ideal for 200 codes)
Soft Assertion won't fail until the end

// Verify All Fields
SoftAssert.softAssert = new SoftAssert();
String actualFirstName = response.jsonPath().getString ("first name")
softAssert.assetEquals = (Sting actual, String expected); // actualFirstName, "Susan", firstName in response is not expected);

int price = response.jsonPath().getInt("totalprice");
softAssert.assertEquals = (price, 440, "total price in response is not expected"

boolean depositPaid = response.jsonPath().getBoolean("depositPaid");
softAssert.assertTrue(depositPaid, "Should be true if it fails");

softAssert.assertAll();


